ary of Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jEGpMqRcQjIC&pg=PA124|year=1996|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-37299-3|pages=124\u2013}}</ref>\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[Erland Josephson]], Swedish actor and director (d. 2012)\n*  1923   &ndash; [[Ninian Stephen]], English-Australian lieutenant, judge, and politician, 20th [[Governor-General of Australia]] (d. 2017)\n*[[1924]] &ndash; [[H\u00e9di Fried]], Swedish author and psychologist \n*  1924   &ndash; [[Ezer Weizman]], Israeli general and politician, 7th [[President of Israel]] (d. 2005)\n*[[1925]] &ndash; [[Richard Baker (broadcaster)|Richard Baker]], English journalist and author (d. 2018)\n*  1925   &ndash; [[Attil\u00e2 \u0130lhan]], Turkish poet, author, and critic (d. 2005)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Alfred Duraiappah]], Sri Lankan Tamil lawyer and politician (d. 1975)\n*[[1927]] &ndash; [[Ross Andru]], American illustrator (d. 1993)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Ibn-e-Insha]], Indian-Pakistani poet and author (d. 1978)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Hugo Pratt]], Italian author and illustrator (d. 1995)\n*[[1930]] &ndash; [[Miguel M\u00e9ndez]], American author and academic (d. 2013)\n*  1930   &ndash; [[Marcel Pronovost]], Canadian ice hockey player and coach (d. 2015)\n*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Joseph Gilbert (RAF officer)|Joseph Gilbert]], English air marshal\n*  1931   &ndash; [[Brian Sewell]], English art dealer and critic (d. 2015)\n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[David Alliance, Baron Alliance]], Iranian-English businessman and politician\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Mario Cuomo]], American lawyer and politician, 52nd [[Governor of New York]] (d. 2015)\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Zia Fariduddin Dagar]], Indian singer (d. 2013)\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Bernie Faloney]], American-Canadian football player and sportscaster (d. 1999)\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Mohammad-Ali Rajai]], Iranian politician, 2nd [[President of Iran]] (d. 1981)\n*  1933   &ndash; [[Predrag Koraksi\u0107 Corax]], Serbian political [[List of caricaturists|caricaturist]]\n*[[1934]