y\u0144ski]], Polish footballer\n*  1992   &ndash; [[Mohamed Salah]], Egyptian footballer\n*  1992   &ndash; [[Dafne Schippers]], Dutch heptathlete and sprinter\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Kanna Arihara]], Japanese singer \n*  1993   &ndash; [[Irfan Had\u017ei\u0107]], Bosnian footballer\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Vincent Janssen]], Dutch footballer\n*  1994   &ndash; [[Inaki Williams]], Basque footballer\n*[[1996]] &ndash; [[Aurora (singer)|Aurora Aksnes]], Norwegian singer-songwriter \n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Madison Kocian]], American gymnast<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teamusa.org/usa-gymnastics/athletes/Madison-Kocian |title=Madison Kocian |publisher=[[United States Olympic Committee]] |accessdate=15 June 2019}}</ref>\n<!--Do not add people without Wikipedia articles to this list. Do not trust \"this year in history\" websites for accurate date information. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence.-->\n\n==Deaths==\n* [[923]] &ndash; [[Robert I of France]] (b. 866)\n* [[948]] &ndash; [[Romanos I|Romanos I Lekapenos]], Byzantine Emperor (b. c. [[870]])\n* [[952]] &ndash; [[Murong Yanchao]], Chinese general\n* [[960]] &ndash; [[Eadburh of Winchester]], English princess and saint\n* [[970]] &ndash; [[Adalbert, Bishop of Passau|Adalbert]], bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Passau|Passau]]\n* [[991]] &ndash; [[Theophanu]], Byzantine wife of [[Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor]] (b. 960)\n*[[1073]] &ndash; [[Emperor Go-Sanj\u014d]] of Japan (b. 1034)\n*[[1184]] &ndash; [[Magnus V of Norway|Magnus Erlingsson]], King of Norway (b. 1156)\n*[[1189]] &ndash; [[Minamoto no Yoshitsune]], Japanese general (b. 1159)\n*[[1246]] &ndash; [[Frederick II, Duke of Austria]] (b. 1219)\n*[[1337]] &ndash; [[Angelo da Clareno]], Italian Franciscan and leader of a group of [[Fraticelli]] (b. 1247)\n*[[1341]] &ndash; [[Andronikos III Palaiologos]], Byzantine emperor (b. 1297)\n*[[1381]] &ndash; [[John Cavendish]], English lawyer and judge (b. 1346)\n*  1381   &nd