ael Blanco]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Ignacio Scocco]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece}} [[Kostas Katsouranis]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.superleaguegreece.net Official website] {{in lang|el}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100312002837/http://www.soccerway.com/national/greece/super-league/2009-2010/regular-season/ 2009\u201310 Super League Greece at Soccerway.com]\n\n{{Superleague Greece}}\n{{2009\u201310 in Greek football}}\n{{2009-10 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{portal bar|Association football|Greece}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2009-10 Superleague Greece}}\n[[Category:Super League Greece seasons]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 in Greek football|1]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 in European association football leagues|Greece]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = [[Superleague Greece]]\n| season           = 2009\u201310\n| winners          = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]<br/>20th title\n| relegated        = [[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]]<br/>[[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]]<br/>[[Panthrakikos F.C.|Panthrakikos]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]<br/>[[PAOK FC|PAOK]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK]]<br/>[[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]<br/>[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| matches          = 252\n| total goals      = 587\n| league topscorer = [[Djibril Ciss\u00e9]] (23)\n| biggest home win = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] 5\u20131 [[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]]<br/>[[Ergotelis F.C.|Ergotelis]] 4\u20130 [[Panthrakikos F.C.|Panthrakikos]]<br/>[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] 4\u20130 [[AEL 1964 FC|AEL]]<br/>[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] 4\u20130 [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]]\n| biggest away win = [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripolis]] 0\u20134 [[Iraklis 1908 Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]\n| highest scoring  = [[Xanthi F.C.|Skoda Xanthi]] 4\u20133 [[Iraklis 1908 Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]] <br> [[Ergotelis F.C.|Ergotelis]] 4\u20133 [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripoli]]\n| prevseason       = [[2008\u201309 Superleague Greece|2008\u201309]]\n| nextseason       = [[2010\u201311 Superleague Greece|2010\u201311]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2009\u201310 [[Superleague Greece]]''' season is the fourth since its establishment. The league consists of 16 teams. Participants are the 13 best teams from the [[2008\u201309 Superleague Greece|2008\u201309]] season and three teams that have been promoted from the [[Beta Ethniki]]. On 11 April 2010, [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] defeated [[Iraklis 1908 Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]] 2\u20130 to secure their 20th Greek title and their first in six years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=gre/news/newsid=1475850.html#panathinaikos+clinch+title |title=Panathinaikos wrap up Greek title |date=2010-04-11 |work=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA]] |accessdate=2010-05-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100414125042/http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association%3Dgre/news/newsid%3D1475850.html |archivedate=14 April 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Changes from 2008\u201309==\n\n===Promotion and relegation===\n'''Teams promoted from [[2008\u201309 Beta Ethniki]]:'''\n* Champions: [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]]\n* Runners-up: [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]]\n* 3rd placed team: [[Kavala F.C.|Kavala]]\n\n'''Teams relegated to [[2009\u201310 Beta Ethniki]]:'''\n* 14th placed team: [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]]\n* 15th placed team: [[Panserraikos F.C.|Panserraikos]]\n* 16th placed team: [[Thrasyvoulos F.C.|Thrasyvoulos]]\n\n===Other changes===\nDue to Greece having ascended in the [[UEFA coefficient#League coefficient|UEFA league coefficient rankings]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xs4all.nl/~kassiesa/bert/uefa/data/method4/crank2009.html|title=UEFA Country Ranking 2009|last=Kassies|first=Bert|accessdate=1 July 2009}}</ref> the 2009\u201310 champions will enter [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League]] at the group stage instead of the third qualifying round. Every other European spot remains unchanged, meaning that the winner of the [[#Play-offs|European play-off group]] will reach the third qualifying round of the Champions League while the runners-up and third-placed team of this group will enter [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League]].\n\n==Team overview==\n\n===Stadia and locations===\n{{Location map+ |Greece |width=380 |float=right |caption=Location of teams in '''2009\u201310 Superleague Greece''' |places=\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=37.966667 |long=23.716667 |label=<small>[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]</small><br><small>[[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]]</small><br><small>[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]</small><br><small>[[Panionios F.C.|Panionios]]</small>}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=40.65     |long=22.9      |label=<small>[[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]</small><br><small>[[Iraklis 1908 Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]</small><br><small>[[PAOK FC|PAOK]]</small>}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=37.516667 |long=22.383333 |label=<small>[[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=35.333333 |long=25.133333 |label=<small>[[Ergotelis F.C.|Ergotelis]]</small>}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=40.933333 |long=24.4      |label=<small>[[Kavala F.C.|Kavala]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=39.641667 |long=22.416667 |label=<small>[[AEL 1964 FC|Larissa]]</small>}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=38.433333 |long=22.866667 |label=<small>[[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]]</small> |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=37.95     |long=23.633333 |label=<small>[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]</small> |position=l